40|$|This {{article focuses}} on the {{triangle}} of intercultural learning – global learning and development education in which DDV International’s work is situated. It outlines the development of <b>intercultural</b> bilingual <b>education</b> {{as well as the}} situation of the indigenous people in Latin America. Some of the indigenous languages are at risk of extinction and with them also the indigenous knowledge attached to it. Once they are lost, intercultural learning through these languages and cultures will not be possible anymore. Drawing on research and some results of the <b>intercultural</b> bilingual <b>education</b> the article highlights the role and importance of intercultural learning, and the potential for empowerment and transformation based on the dialogue between the indigenous and western cultures that occurs in development work...|$|R
